  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of treatment with AICS is weaning from oral corticosteroids, i.e. a reduction of the
      oral corticosteroid dose. An anticipated treatment benefit of AICS is a reduction of oral
      corticosteroid dose and stability/improvement of clinical parameters related to asthma in the
      targeted subject population. Ultimately, the goal is to free subjects with severe asthma from
      the burden of chronic oral steroid therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
